# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================
# This .dockerignore file significantly reduces:
# 1. Build context transfer time to Docker daemon
# 2. Final image size
# 3. Security risks (no credentials, no .git history)
#
# What IS included in the image:
# - Python source code (*.py)
# - Configuration files (config/)
# - Static assets (assets/)
# - Data files (data/) - if needed
# - pyproject.toml (dependencies)
# - README.md
# - .docker/Dockerfile, entrypoint.sh, healthcheck.sh
#
# Best Practices:
# - Review this file when adding new directories/files
# - Use .dockerignore patterns similar to .gitignore
# - Mount sensitive data as volumes at runtime
# - Keep images minimal and focused
# ============================================================================
